doubt, and insecurity. Inspired to unmake their poems so that they might remake them, these poets welcomed discomposition because it catalyzed ongoing thinking and learning. Blotted Lines brings literary scholarship into conversation with modern composition studies, challenging early modern literary studies to treat writing as both noun and verb and foregrounding the ways poetry and criticism alike can model for students the cultivation of patience, collaboration, and risk in their writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy16th century. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy17th century. 0aPoeticsxHistoryy18th century. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aPoetry & Criticism. 70(DE-588)4014777-00(DE-627)1063387490(DE-576)208909400aEnglisch2gnd 70(DE-588)4035964-50(DE-627)1062450150(DE-576)209015608aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-588)4036774-50(DE-627)1041377890(DE-576)209020326aLyrik2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  awriting practices in early modern England, teaching writing in the literature classroom, invention of literary studies, writing poetry, Shakespeare, early modern literary studies, early modern poetics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501769863?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps